Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(diced) into small pieces. Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice lengthways into thin strips then chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Bring a #saucepan{} of water to boil for the pasta. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @lamb mince{200%g} and cook until golden brown all over, ~{4-5%minutes}, using a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Add the onion and carrot and cook until they beginning to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @tomatoes with basil{1}(finely chopped) and @ground cinnamon{1%tsp} (add less if you're not a fan of it!) with the @water for the sauce{150%ml} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Add @sugar{pinch}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring regularly, until thick and tomatoey, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boiling water and add the @rigatoni pasta{200%g}. Cook for ~{12%minutes} then drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with a little @oil{} to prevent it from sticking together.

While everything cooks, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} into small pieces.

Taste the lamb sauce and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} to taste. Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it needs it. Stir the drained pasta and half the parsley through the sauce then divide between plates. Top with the crumbled feta and remaining parsley. Enjoy!